c setion mamas only hey mama i had my baby friday and ended having to get a c section any tips on how you slept and got over the soreness i have had three walk as much as you can the more you move the faster you will heal but don't walk so much that you are really bad pain quit when you start to feel tired keep up on the pain pills don't wait for the pain to come completely back don't do any heavy lifting though please don't clean your house by your self no vacuuming i learned this the hard way a pillow pressed up against your tummy is soothing especially when nursing so baby doesn't wiggle and hit your cut as far as sleeping goes i found a body pillow was still very useful after my sections just take it easy and don't do to much good news if you have to have another c section it is easier to heal everytime Breastfeeding Mattress Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Equine conformation Upholstery The McGuire Sisters Cliff Richard Diving AFI 100 Years series Strap-on dildo Sandy Koufax Humphrey Bogart EastEnders Leo Wyatt Prostate cancer Cher (entertainer) Friends Knots Landing Rosa Parks Jam (TV series) Kodocha Kurt Cobain Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Single certification The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Care Bears Weight training Alanis Morissette Aerial (dance move) The Shining (film) Michael Jackson Spice Girls Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) First aid Operation Market Garden Breech birth The Invisibles Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Sleeping Murder Shaggy dog story Jon Secada The Jazz Singer Childbirth Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Bon Jovi Professional wrestling slang Reflexology Knife The Cure Mouse (computing) Dietary fiber Massage Fecal incontinence Joke Drill bit Piccolo Junior Saga Social rule Daz Dillinger Clinical depression Everwood Nipple piercing Stomach cancer John Lennon Saga (band) Tenshinhan The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Psoriasis Professional wrestling holds Smallville (Season 4) Pitaten Babe Ruth Futurama (TV se